<h1>@HI{{gotoni}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{gotoni}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{gotoni}}</strong> is used to indicate that something happens regularly at a certain spacing in time or space.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{three^time^interval}}<strong>gotoni</strong>@KJ{{medicine}}wo@KJ{{drink}}mimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I took medicine every three hours.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{correct^month}}ha@KJ{{house}}<strong>gotoni</strong>@KJ{{gate^pine*tree}}wo@KJ{{stand*up}}temasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      They put up pine tree decorations at every house on New Year's Day.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

